graph.packing

Class BBNode2

  • java.lang.Object
    • graph.packing.BBNodeBase
      • graph.packing.BBNode2
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Comparable, java.lang.Runnable

    class BBNode2
extends BBNodeBase
    represents a node in the B&B tree of the hybrid B&B - GASP scheme for the 2-packing problem. It implements the Comparable interface as BBNode2 objects enter a priority queue (BBQueue) from which nodes are selected for processing (passing them to the BBThreadPool that is a proxy for a parallel.FasterParallelAsynchBatchTaskExecutor executor). It also implements the Runnable interface as the executor requires runnable objects to process.

    Title: popt4jlib

    Description: A Parallel Meta-Heuristic Optimization Library in Java

        Sole constructor of a BBNode2 object. Clients are not expected to create such objects which are instead created dynamically through the B&B process.
        Parameters:
        master - BBTree the master BBTree object of which this is a node.
        r - Set Set<Node> the set of (graph) nodes to be added to the nodes of the parent to represent a new partial solution.
        parent - BBNode2 the parent BB-node in the B&B tree construction process.
        Throws:
        PackingException - if the second argument is non-null but the third argument is null.

      • getBound

        protected double getBound()
                   throws ParallelException
        compute a max. possible number of nodes this soln can have One such bound is _nodes.size() + (gsz - getForbiddenNodes().size()) A better bound is _nodes.size() + #unconnectednodes + #(remainingopennodes)/min.{NNbors.size()} An even better is to compute the NNborsOpen.size() for each node and divide by this number+1 (so that the total nodes with only one open NNbor are divided by two when considering the bound as a sum, and so on).
        Specified by:
        getBound in class BBNodeBase
